<br>
Our main loot awarding system is PiPo (Points in - Points out), which is similar to DKP, but seems to lessen the spread between the ultra hardcore raiders and the more casual raiders.<br>
<br>
We also do officer awarded loot for items which are deemed not good enough to spend points on, or are off mobs which are deemed too easy to be getting points for killing it.<br>
<br>
If no-one wants to spend points on an item, then it becomes open to high level twinks (Typically toons that are 2 boxed a lot on raids) or invites.<br>
<br>
However, on very rare occasions at the officer's discretion the points system can be overriden if we feel that a particular item really should go to a certain character. If this happens, the person who would have normally gotten the item is talked to privately, asking them to voluntarily step aside and giving them the reason why. So far we haven't had anyone refuse to step aside, so I don't know what we'd do if we did <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
System has worked pretty well for us so far, can't really think of any complaints. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13112"><img src="http://xtctripp101.homestead.com/files/Sigs/Mordi_Sig.gif"></a><br>Overlord<br>
